1
00:00:10,133 --> 00:00:12,000
Prices are so high these days.

2
00:00:12,133 --> 00:00:14,367
I can't even put a nice meal
on our family's table.

3
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:17,167
And the money I was saving
for my own tricycle?

4
00:00:17,300 --> 00:00:18,367
I was scammed.

5
00:00:19,733 --> 00:00:20,800
- What's wrong?
- Uh...

6
00:00:20,933 --> 00:00:22,800
- I forgot something.
- Wait!

7
00:00:22,933 --> 00:00:25,133
King, I need you to stay here
while I work, okay?

8
00:00:25,267 --> 00:00:26,167
King!

9
00:00:26,300 --> 00:00:27,233
What's going on?

10
00:00:27,367 --> 00:00:28,833
King's gone missing!

11
00:00:28,967 --> 00:00:31,100
I know you're still
searching for your son.

12
00:00:31,233 --> 00:00:32,667
The colonel and I can help you.

13
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:35,833
We need to show him
we're on his side.

14
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:37,667
I found King.

15
00:00:37,800 --> 00:00:39,433
I managed to save him myself.

16
00:00:40,100 --> 00:00:41,000
He's safe.

17
00:00:41,133 --> 00:00:42,367
Agnes, thank you.

18
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:44,467
- Thank you! Please take care.
- No big deal.

19
00:00:44,600 --> 00:00:46,467
Chief, can we get a picture?

20
00:00:46,600 --> 00:00:48,167
- Chief! Chief!
- Of course!

21
00:00:48,300 --> 00:00:49,733
Dad!

22
00:00:50,333 --> 00:00:51,533
Dad!

23
00:00:52,500 --> 00:00:53,667
Dad!

24
00:00:54,467 --> 00:00:57,300
Lay a hand on my family again,

25
00:00:57,433 --> 00:00:59,567
and I will blow my brains out.

26
00:00:59,700 --> 00:01:01,200
And with my death,

27
00:01:01,333 --> 00:01:04,167
your hopes of ever getting your
 money back will die with me.

28
00:01:04,300 --> 00:01:06,200
Leave me alone,

29
00:01:06,333 --> 00:01:08,733
and I will cooperate with you.

30
00:01:17,267 --> 00:01:20,033
Don't ever fail me again!

31
00:01:21,133 --> 00:01:23,033
Because if you fail
to retrieve the money,

32
00:01:23,167 --> 00:01:25,700
I'll send you and your brother
straight to hell.

33
00:01:28,733 --> 00:01:30,300
What's with all the bruises
on his face?

34
00:01:30,433 --> 00:01:31,700
He showed up today.

35
00:01:33,967 --> 00:01:35,000
What's he up to?

36
00:01:44,233 --> 00:01:51,100
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

37
00:02:09,733 --> 00:02:12,933
[MOTORCYCLE ENGINE REVVING]

38
00:02:13,067 --> 00:02:19,700
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

39
00:02:19,867 --> 00:02:23,100
[LOLITA] I trusted you
 with my grandson!

40
00:02:23,233 --> 00:02:26,667
If anything happens to him,
God help me,

41
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:29,400
I don't know
what I'll do to you!

42
00:02:29,533 --> 00:02:31,700
[SAMUEL]
 Please don't hurt my son!

43
00:02:31,833 --> 00:02:33,700
[LOLITA CRYING] My grandson!

44
00:02:33,833 --> 00:02:37,967
[KING SOBBING]
Dad, please come and rescue me!

45
00:02:38,100 --> 00:02:40,167
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

46
00:02:40,300 --> 00:02:41,400
[CAR HORN HONKING]

47
00:02:41,533 --> 00:02:42,500
Sam--

48
00:02:42,633 --> 00:02:46,167
[CAR PASSING BY]

49
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:51,367
[CAR HORN HONKING]

50
00:02:51,500 --> 00:02:52,567
[ARISSA GRUNTS]

51
00:02:54,367 --> 00:03:01,200
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

52
00:03:12,167 --> 00:03:13,367
[ARISSA] I'm sorry, King.

53
00:03:13,500 --> 00:03:15,000
I need to do this.

54
00:03:15,767 --> 00:03:17,567
Samuel shouldn't have to carry
the consequences

55
00:03:17,700 --> 00:03:19,500
of our father's actions alone.

56
00:03:20,300 --> 00:03:23,967
I need to figure out a way
to help him.

57
00:03:27,600 --> 00:03:28,600
- Sir.
- What?

58
00:03:28,733 --> 00:03:30,033
You look handsome
in this picture.

59
00:03:30,467 --> 00:03:32,200
Of course, that's my good angle.

60
00:03:33,333 --> 00:03:35,300
- Any other pictures of me?
- See for  yourself.

61
00:03:35,433 --> 00:03:36,767
[TELEPHONE RINGING
IN THE DISTANCE]

62
00:03:36,900 --> 00:03:37,633
Nice.

63
00:03:37,767 --> 00:03:38,733
Send these to me.

64
00:03:38,867 --> 00:03:40,100
[CHUCKLES] Sure thing, sir.

65
00:03:42,867 --> 00:03:45,600
By the way,
any news from Espera?

66
00:03:46,433 --> 00:03:48,833
Yeah, about that...
Their responses were vague.

67
00:03:48,967 --> 00:03:50,900
Apparently, the case
is top-secret,

68
00:03:51,033 --> 00:03:53,533
so they couldn't say anything.

69
00:03:54,367 --> 00:03:58,200
How serious is this case
to warrant a special operation?

70
00:03:58,333 --> 00:04:01,000
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

71
00:04:01,133 --> 00:04:04,800
What makes it different
from other kidnapping incidents?

72
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:06,633
I'm curious, too.

73
00:04:07,867 --> 00:04:11,200
Also, the kid's house doesn't
look like it belongs

74
00:04:11,333 --> 00:04:12,567
to a wealthy family.

75
00:04:12,700 --> 00:04:14,767
Where would they've gotten
the ransom money, right?

76
00:04:14,900 --> 00:04:17,867
Don't you think it's connected
to his father's case?

77
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,667
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

78
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:21,867
What's really going on
with that family?

79
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:26,167
What secrets does he keep?

80
00:04:31,267 --> 00:04:32,200
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

81
00:04:32,333 --> 00:04:34,233
Is Johnny Policarpio here?

82
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:36,667
Uh, ma'am...

83
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:38,400
I'm PO2 Johnny Policarpio.

84
00:04:38,533 --> 00:04:40,200
How can I be of service?

85
00:05:04,400 --> 00:05:11,233
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

86
00:05:13,433 --> 00:05:14,300
[LOCKER DOOR OPENS]

87
00:05:15,667 --> 00:05:16,733
[LOCKER DOOR CLOSES]

88
00:05:26,733 --> 00:05:27,667
[ARISSA GRUNTS]

89
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:34,833
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

90
00:05:49,400 --> 00:05:56,233
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

91
00:06:00,533 --> 00:06:01,900
This should be good.

92
00:06:03,567 --> 00:06:04,767
For now.

93
00:06:12,933 --> 00:06:14,000
[CUP THUDS]

94
00:06:17,367 --> 00:06:20,667
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

95
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:22,133
Thank you.

96
00:06:22,867 --> 00:06:25,067
I owe you my son's life.

97
00:06:27,167 --> 00:06:28,067
I--

98
00:06:31,767 --> 00:06:32,833
[AGNES CLEARS THROAT]

99
00:06:35,333 --> 00:06:42,200
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

100
00:06:48,900 --> 00:06:50,300
King told me something.

101
00:06:50,433 --> 00:06:54,000
Apparently, there was
this who angel rescued him.

102
00:06:55,767 --> 00:06:56,933
That was you.

103
00:06:58,500 --> 00:06:59,833
Thank you.

104
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:03,667
Do you still remember what
you told me that night?

105
00:07:04,500 --> 00:07:07,600
That I would never understand
you because I'm not a mother?

106
00:07:07,733 --> 00:07:09,367
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

107
00:07:09,500 --> 00:07:10,500
Samuel...

108
00:07:13,167 --> 00:07:14,467
Trust me.

109
00:07:15,533 --> 00:07:17,033
I do understand you.

110
00:07:18,267 --> 00:07:24,667
Every parent just wants
their kid to be safe.

111
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:26,100
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

112
00:07:26,233 --> 00:07:29,233
You know, when I found King,

113
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:32,167
all I could think about

114
00:07:33,367 --> 00:07:36,000
was making sure he was okay
and getting him back to you.

115
00:07:39,533 --> 00:07:40,767
Because of him,

116
00:07:41,500 --> 00:07:46,767
I remembered why I chose
to help the colonel.

117
00:07:46,900 --> 00:07:48,467
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

118
00:07:48,633 --> 00:07:52,267
No matter how impossible
or dangerous my mission is,

119
00:07:54,233 --> 00:07:58,200
I do it for kids like him.

120
00:08:00,467 --> 00:08:03,233
Because deep down,
I wanted to do something

121
00:08:03,900 --> 00:08:05,500
I wish I could've done...

122
00:08:06,400 --> 00:08:08,000
for my own child.

123
00:08:08,133 --> 00:08:10,967
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

124
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:12,833
[INHALES DEEPLY, CLEARS THROAT]

125
00:08:13,700 --> 00:08:15,833
Uh, anyway...

126
00:08:17,833 --> 00:08:19,300
What are you still doing here?

127
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:21,633
What are you planning?

128
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:22,733
They might hurt--

129
00:08:22,867 --> 00:08:24,167
[BEKKAH] Agnes, girl!

130
00:08:24,300 --> 00:08:26,000
Take a look!
It's your husband!

131
00:08:26,133 --> 00:08:28,367
See? He's famous now!

132
00:08:28,500 --> 00:08:30,933
[REPORTER] It appears it wasn't
part of the operation.

133
00:08:31,067 --> 00:08:33,467
What would you say
to those criticizing you

134
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:35,367
for breaking protocol?

135
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:37,633
[JOHNNY]
 It all happened way too fast.

136
00:08:38,367 --> 00:08:39,900
I mean, time wasn't on our side.

137
00:08:40,033 --> 00:08:42,233
When I saw that boy,
I knew what had to be done.

138
00:08:42,367 --> 00:08:44,700
It was a dangerous place,
so I rescued him.

139
00:08:44,833 --> 00:08:46,333
As a police officer,

140
00:08:47,033 --> 00:08:49,667
I'm always ready for anything.

141
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:52,067
Saving lives is
my bread and butter.

142
00:08:52,733 --> 00:08:55,600
So, I have no regrets.

143
00:08:56,300 --> 00:08:58,033
I did the right thing,

144
00:08:58,167 --> 00:09:00,267
even if it meant facing backlash
 for rescuing

145
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:05,867
the son of the infamous scammer,
 Samuel Trinidad.

146
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:07,733
What would you say
to those accusing you

147
00:09:07,867 --> 00:09:10,133
of being a protector
of criminals,

148
00:09:10,267 --> 00:09:11,667
particularly in relation
to the incident

149
00:09:11,800 --> 00:09:13,267
involving Samuel Trinidad's son,

150
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:17,367
who is allegedly linked to his
father Mike Trinidad's case?

151
00:09:17,500 --> 00:09:19,400
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

152
00:09:19,533 --> 00:09:21,933
First of all,
to those saying that...

153
00:09:22,067 --> 00:09:23,567
I don't care what you think.

154
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:26,300
He's just a child.

155
00:09:27,033 --> 00:09:28,900
He has nothing to do
with the mistakes

156
00:09:29,067 --> 00:09:30,700
of his father or grandfather.

157
00:09:31,733 --> 00:09:34,933
Second, it's our duty
as police officers

158
00:09:35,067 --> 00:09:36,300
to protect the innocent.

159
00:09:36,933 --> 00:09:37,933
Right?

160
00:09:38,067 --> 00:09:39,533
But don't worry.

161
00:09:40,333 --> 00:09:42,500
I'll investigate this case,

162
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:45,267
and I won't stop...

163
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:48,567
until I find the mastermind

164
00:09:48,700 --> 00:09:50,633
behind this kidnapping incident.

165
00:09:50,767 --> 00:09:54,800
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

166
00:09:54,933 --> 00:09:56,467
- Jacob.
- Hmm?

167
00:09:57,333 --> 00:09:59,333
Make sure we don't get dragged
into this.

168
00:10:00,967 --> 00:10:02,367
I'll make sure of it.

169
00:10:03,067 --> 00:10:04,767
No one involved
will live another day.

170
00:10:05,633 --> 00:10:09,233
Really now? Because I remember
one of your boys getting away.

171
00:10:09,367 --> 00:10:11,367
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

172
00:10:11,500 --> 00:10:12,267
[SCOFFS]

173
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:14,600
I'm sure he won't rat us out.

174
00:10:17,100 --> 00:10:18,000
[ROLDAN] And that cop?

175
00:10:18,733 --> 00:10:21,700
Make sure he doesn't find
any dirt on us.

176
00:10:21,833 --> 00:10:23,900
[MUSIC BECOMES SINISTER]

177
00:10:24,033 --> 00:10:26,200
Okay. Okay.

178
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:30,867
[FINGER TAPPING ON TABLE]

179
00:10:31,667 --> 00:10:33,700
You never told us
your husband's such a looker!

180
00:10:33,833 --> 00:10:35,167
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

181
00:10:35,333 --> 00:10:37,133
[BEKKAH] Your son was
the kidnapping victim?

182
00:10:37,267 --> 00:10:40,500
The one saved by Agnes's
good-looking husband?

183
00:10:40,633 --> 00:10:43,900
If that's the case,
why do you look so beaten up?

184
00:10:44,033 --> 00:10:45,633
Are you just a troublemaker
at heart?

185
00:10:46,433 --> 00:10:47,200
Goodness.

186
00:10:47,333 --> 00:10:49,200
What a world we're living in.

187
00:10:50,267 --> 00:10:57,300
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

188
00:11:03,133 --> 00:11:06,367
- I can't believe that happened.
- I feel sorry for him.

189
00:11:06,500 --> 00:11:08,567
[EMPLOYEE 1] Oh. Sir Samuel.

190
00:11:08,733 --> 00:11:10,433
Sorry about what
happened to your son.

191
00:11:10,567 --> 00:11:12,067
I hope he's okay now.

192
00:11:13,033 --> 00:11:15,467
[EMPLOYEE 2] I admire your
hard work, sir.

193
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:19,733
You still came to work despite
what you're going through.

194
00:11:19,867 --> 00:11:21,733
Did you get that bruise
from the incident?

195
00:11:21,867 --> 00:11:23,433
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

196
00:11:23,567 --> 00:11:24,467
Uh...

197
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:28,500
Um...

198
00:11:29,867 --> 00:11:32,267
Excuse me. Thank you.

199
00:11:34,967 --> 00:11:36,933
Poor guy.

200
00:11:38,133 --> 00:11:40,467
[REPORTER ON VIDEO]
 What can you say about people

201
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:42,067
calling you the protector
of criminals

202
00:11:42,233 --> 00:11:45,167
after saving the son
of Samuel Trinidad,

203
00:11:45,300 --> 00:11:47,067
who has been linked
to a scam

204
00:11:47,200 --> 00:11:49,533
involving his father,
Mike Trinidad?

205
00:11:49,667 --> 00:11:52,900
I don't care
what people say.

206
00:11:53,033 --> 00:11:54,667
I mean, he's just a kid.

207
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:56,133
The kid has nothing
to do

208
00:11:56,267 --> 00:11:59,000
with what his father
and grandfather did.

209
00:11:59,133 --> 00:12:02,767
And as a cop, it's our duty
to protect people.

210
00:12:02,900 --> 00:12:04,133
But don't worry.

211
00:12:04,267 --> 00:12:06,133
I'll investigate
this matter.

212
00:12:06,267 --> 00:12:09,767
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

213
00:12:09,900 --> 00:12:12,400
According to PO2
Johnny Policarpio,

214
00:12:12,533 --> 00:12:16,700
Samuel Trinidad's son is now
safe from the kidnappers.

215
00:12:16,867 --> 00:12:20,067
However, NLEA will continue
to conduct an investigation

216
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:22,733
to determine the persons behind
 the kidnapping incident.

217
00:12:22,867 --> 00:12:29,900
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

218
00:12:34,200 --> 00:12:38,200
Ma, just keep me posted
if something happens, okay?

219
00:12:38,967 --> 00:12:40,467
Take care.

220
00:12:40,600 --> 00:12:41,667
You all take care.

221
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:44,633
- [INHALES SHARPLY]
- [PHONE THUDS]

222
00:12:45,867 --> 00:12:50,867
[BREATHING SHARPLY]

223
00:12:51,033 --> 00:12:55,667
[BLADE SWISHING]

224
00:12:55,800 --> 00:13:02,633
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

225
00:13:04,567 --> 00:13:05,967
You're unbelievable.

226
00:13:08,100 --> 00:13:09,533
Your son was
kidnapped, right?

227
00:13:11,133 --> 00:13:13,467
And yet you reported
for work.

228
00:13:17,267 --> 00:13:19,633
Because I shouldn't
stop living my life...

229
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:22,600
for people like them.

230
00:13:22,733 --> 00:13:23,633
Oh.

231
00:13:25,867 --> 00:13:27,367
"Them?"

232
00:13:27,500 --> 00:13:28,733
[JACOB SNICKERS]

233
00:13:28,867 --> 00:13:30,800
Who are you
talking about?

234
00:13:30,933 --> 00:13:36,900
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

235
00:13:37,033 --> 00:13:39,467
Do you know the people who
kidnapped your son?

236
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:43,600
They're not humans.

237
00:13:46,567 --> 00:13:48,667
For me...

238
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:50,900
I consider them scums.

239
00:13:51,033 --> 00:13:54,600
They're scums
who are up to no good...

240
00:13:56,067 --> 00:13:57,600
and don't deserve
to live.

241
00:14:00,133 --> 00:14:01,633
I see you're tough.

242
00:14:01,767 --> 00:14:05,200
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

243
00:14:05,333 --> 00:14:07,233
It's as if
you're not afraid.

244
00:14:11,233 --> 00:14:13,567
Do you know who
you're going up against?

245
00:14:13,700 --> 00:14:14,600
Me? Afraid?

246
00:14:17,633 --> 00:14:19,200
I'm not afraid.

247
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:25,033
When it comes to my son
and my family,

248
00:14:25,167 --> 00:14:27,067
I'm not afraid
of anything.

249
00:14:28,633 --> 00:14:29,500
And besides...

250
00:14:31,033 --> 00:14:33,200
I'm sure those people
are cowards.

251
00:14:35,400 --> 00:14:38,567
Because only cowards
move in the dark.

252
00:14:40,333 --> 00:14:43,900
They're scared to show up
and face me.

253
00:14:44,033 --> 00:14:45,133
They fight discreetly.

254
00:14:45,267 --> 00:14:52,300
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

255
00:14:55,367 --> 00:14:58,067
Well, sir,
if you don't mind,

256
00:14:58,200 --> 00:15:01,100
I'm paid every minute
that I'm here.

257
00:15:01,267 --> 00:15:02,733
I have to go back
to work.

258
00:15:03,900 --> 00:15:05,333
Please excuse me.

259
00:15:05,467 --> 00:15:12,500
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

260
00:15:19,067 --> 00:15:26,100
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

261
00:15:29,333 --> 00:15:36,200
[GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

262
00:15:40,567 --> 00:15:42,100
Oh.

263
00:15:42,233 --> 00:15:47,533
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

264
00:15:47,667 --> 00:15:50,667
Poor kid! He even got kidnapped.

265
00:15:51,667 --> 00:15:53,967
This is too much.

266
00:15:54,100 --> 00:15:56,167
That kid didn't do
anything wrong.

267
00:15:56,300 --> 00:15:57,133
Tsk.

268
00:15:58,233 --> 00:16:00,633
You know, ever since
that scandal exploded,

269
00:16:01,567 --> 00:16:03,300
their family keeps
getting in danger.

270
00:16:04,367 --> 00:16:06,133
[SIGHS] I feel guilty.

271
00:16:07,467 --> 00:16:09,767
Because I was one of those
who angrily attacked them.

272
00:16:09,933 --> 00:16:14,800
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

273
00:16:14,933 --> 00:16:17,300
Isn't this the apartment
they moved into?

274
00:16:18,667 --> 00:16:19,900
- Look.
- Oh.

275
00:16:21,067 --> 00:16:22,233
- You're right.
- See?

276
00:16:24,800 --> 00:16:27,133
Oh no, love.
The people will mob them.

277
00:16:28,033 --> 00:16:29,533
I need to warn them, love.

278
00:16:29,667 --> 00:16:36,700
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

279
00:16:44,700 --> 00:16:45,833
Arissa.

280
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:49,800
How's King?
I heard he's been rescued.

281
00:16:50,700 --> 00:16:51,933
He's fine, but...

282
00:16:53,233 --> 00:16:54,167
not so much.

283
00:17:00,800 --> 00:17:03,100
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

284
00:17:03,233 --> 00:17:04,133
Arissa.

285
00:17:05,933 --> 00:17:07,300
I'm sorry for asking, but...

286
00:17:09,167 --> 00:17:11,667
does this have something to do
with what your dad did?

287
00:17:15,633 --> 00:17:17,433
Dad wasn't even around much,
you know.

288
00:17:17,567 --> 00:17:20,200
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

289
00:17:20,333 --> 00:17:21,767
When he was still alive,

290
00:17:21,900 --> 00:17:22,800
I could only feel his presence

291
00:17:22,933 --> 00:17:24,867
because of his
financial support.

292
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:26,433
But now that he's gone,

293
00:17:26,567 --> 00:17:27,867
I could still feel his presence

294
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:30,267
because we're the ones
paying for his sins.

295
00:17:30,400 --> 00:17:37,233
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

296
00:17:39,233 --> 00:17:41,300
You know, sometimes,
dads can really be a headache.

297
00:17:49,933 --> 00:17:52,867
Just forget what I said.
It's nothing.

298
00:17:55,600 --> 00:18:02,433
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

299
00:18:14,667 --> 00:18:16,700
Samuel is really
getting on my nerves.

300
00:18:16,833 --> 00:18:18,333
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

301
00:18:18,467 --> 00:18:21,333
Roldan, just let me
torture his sister.

302
00:18:21,500 --> 00:18:23,233
Come on, let me torture her!

303
00:18:24,600 --> 00:18:25,933
If you do that,

304
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:29,233
it'll be even harder for us
to get the money.

305
00:18:33,633 --> 00:18:34,533
Be patient.

306
00:18:34,667 --> 00:18:36,200
[SCOFFS]

307
00:18:36,333 --> 00:18:38,033
Remember what he told us?

308
00:18:38,167 --> 00:18:39,167
He said...

309
00:18:39,633 --> 00:18:41,900
just leave him alone,

310
00:18:42,967 --> 00:18:45,233
and he'd return the money to us.

311
00:18:45,367 --> 00:18:47,267
So... [SCOFFS]

312
00:18:47,400 --> 00:18:49,133
you believe that bastard?

313
00:18:50,767 --> 00:18:54,133
How can we be sure he won't
run away with the money?

314
00:18:55,533 --> 00:18:57,400
Will you just let him
toy with us?

315
00:18:57,533 --> 00:18:58,867
Come on, Roldan!

316
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:00,767
I'm willing to play the game

317
00:19:00,900 --> 00:19:03,300
than take the risk
and pay the price.

318
00:19:04,567 --> 00:19:06,600
If you make Samuel mad,

319
00:19:06,733 --> 00:19:10,533
we'll never get the money
we worked hard for.

320
00:19:10,667 --> 00:19:11,733
Is that what you want?

321
00:19:14,267 --> 00:19:15,200
And, Jacob...

322
00:19:16,367 --> 00:19:18,867
don't question my decisions.

323
00:19:19,733 --> 00:19:21,133
Remember,

324
00:19:21,267 --> 00:19:23,133
all this mess wouldn't
have happened

325
00:19:23,267 --> 00:19:25,300
if you and your lapdog
didn't screw up!

326
00:19:25,433 --> 00:19:32,300
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

327
00:19:40,567 --> 00:19:42,833
Eat up, sweetie.

328
00:19:44,100 --> 00:19:45,800
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

329
00:19:45,933 --> 00:19:46,667
Move!

330
00:19:46,800 --> 00:19:51,300
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

331
00:19:51,433 --> 00:19:52,500
Miss Lolita!

332
00:19:54,300 --> 00:19:55,167
Miss Lolita!

333
00:19:58,167 --> 00:19:59,067
Hold on!

334
00:20:00,867 --> 00:20:02,367
- Yes?
- They're coming.

335
00:20:02,533 --> 00:20:03,700
They know where you live.

336
00:20:03,833 --> 00:20:07,400
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

337
00:20:07,533 --> 00:20:09,633
- Hey!
- [MAEL] Wait a minute!

338
00:20:09,767 --> 00:20:13,000
Get out! Show yourselves!
Scammers!

339
00:20:14,467 --> 00:20:16,533
[MAEL] What are you doing
 here?! Hey!

340
00:20:16,667 --> 00:20:18,300
[CLAMORING]

341
00:20:18,433 --> 00:20:20,867
- Hey! Stop!
- Don't do this!

342
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:27,967
- [TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [CLAMORING]

343
00:20:30,167 --> 00:20:36,667
[SHOUTING, CLAMORING]

344
00:20:36,833 --> 00:20:42,600
[TENSE MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

345
00:20:44,333 --> 00:20:45,267
This Wednesday...

346
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:47,267
Please! No!

347
00:20:47,400 --> 00:20:50,867
We don't care if your grandson
gets kidnapped!

348
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:52,767
You have crossed
the line!

349
00:20:52,900 --> 00:20:57,100
An act of heroism
will unleash chaos.

350
00:20:57,233 --> 00:20:59,167
Their family
is in danger again.

351
00:20:59,300 --> 00:21:00,967
Johnny, this isn't just
about you.

352
00:21:01,100 --> 00:21:03,300
Then who is it about?!
Samuel?!

353
00:21:03,433 --> 00:21:05,833
I need to make sure
my family is safe.

354
00:21:05,967 --> 00:21:07,233
We need to get away
from here.

355
00:21:07,367 --> 00:21:09,867
I want to push him
to his limits.

356
00:21:10,033 --> 00:21:12,000
Dad!
